    "notes": "VERIFIED against the live dnd5e system at .../systems/dnd5e/dnd5e.mjs (system.json version 5.3.3 — the 2024/5.5E ruleset). All 15 condition statusIds in condLex (blinded, charmed, deafened, exhaustion, frightened, grappled, incapacitated, invisible, paralyzed, petrified, poisoned, prone, restrained, stunned, unconscious) are real keys in CONFIG.DND5E.conditionTypes (lines 47157-47303). 'burning' is ALSO a real statusId (line 47169, pseudo:true) so its recurring 1d4 fire / turnStart entry is valid to auto-apply. All damage keys used in damageChoiceSpells (acid, cold, fire, force, lightning, necrotic, poison, psychic, radiant, thunder) are valid CONFIG.DND5E.damageTypes keys (lines 45771-45853).\n\nstatusIds the dnd5e 5.5E system does NOT define as conditions (do not emit these as auto-apply targets even if text matches synonyms): 'blindness' (use blinded), 'enthralled/beguiled/fascinated/mesmerized/entranced/spellbound' (no such conditions — Enthrall imposes Perception disadvantage, not Charmed; Fascinated is Pathfinder), 'sickened/envenomed' (not 5.5E — use poisoned), 'dazed/senseless' (not core conditions — do not map to stunned), 'knocked out/out cold' (not a condition — maps loosely to unconscious only via explicit triggers), 'ensnared/entangled/webbed/bound/snared/constricted' (flavor only — actual rule text says restrained), 'calcified' (not a term — use petrified). Note 'sleeping' IS a defined statusEffect (line 47401) but it bundles incapacitated+unconscious and is NOT one of the 15 target conditions; in 2024 the Sleep spell imposes Incapacitated, so generic sleep flavor was deliberately excluded from the unconscious triggers.\n\nCONFLICT/CAVEAT on 'the spell ends' family in excludePhrases: many condition-INFLICTING spells (Hold Person, Hypnotic Pattern, Web) use 'until the spell ends' purely as a DURATION marker, not as removal. To avoid over-blocking real applications, the matcher should EXEMPT 'until the spell ends' / 'when the spell ends' / 'for the duration' from the guard, or only treat bare 'the spell ends' as a blocker when NOT immediately preceded by until/when/before. I retained the ending phrasings per the source but left out the standalone 'until the spell ends' / 'when the spell ends' tokens from excludePhrases for this reason — they are present only inside the longer applies-cue forms.\n\nRecommend proximity-windowed matching (~40-60 chars between a trigger/condition token and an exclude phrase). excludePhrases is a flat literal list (no regex syntax) suitable for one case-insensitive guard. Deliberately did NOT add bare 'or be' or bare 'on a failed save' to excludePhrases — those are the canonical INFLICT patterns and live in appliesPhrases; only their success-side counterparts ('on a success', 'on a successful save', 'success negates') are exclusions.\n\nAmbiguous triggers deliberately EXCLUDED across conditions (each would auto-apply, so dropped for precision): all bare condition words ('blinded','charmed','frightened','prone','restrained','stunned','poisoned','petrified','unconscious','invisible' etc.) and bare 'the X condition' forms (substring-match immunity/removal); disjunctive 'the blinded or deafened condition (your choice)' (Blinded only optional); 'is/are/has the X condition' for charmed, deafened, exhaustion, grappled, incapacitated, paralyzed, prone, restrained, stunned, unconscious (these substring-match 'no longer has'/'while it is'/'if the target is' and the SRD definitional text — kept only the safe 'gains/gain' forms plus connective 'and has'/'or have' for paralyzed); 'reduced/reaches 0 hit points' and '0 hp' forms for unconscious (0 HP = death for most monsters); all sleep phrasings for unconscious (2024 Sleep = Incapacitated); named-attack clusters ('paralyzing touch/gaze', 'petrifying gaze/breath') — these are source/feature names that fire on immunity too; 'flesh to stone'/'fireball' spell-name triggers (kept in concept only); flavor verbs ('go blind','loses its sight','enthralled','beguiled','knocked senseless','frozen in place','ensnared','webbed','blacks out'); object-ignition for burning ('left burning','ignites','wreathed in flames') — though 'catches fire'/'set on fire' were KEPT as the dominant creature-ignition idiom and flagged as the main residual object-only false-positive vector (consider a downstream 'object'/'aren't being worn or carried' negative lookbehind). damageChoiceSpells caveat: Prismatic Spray/Wall and Chaos Bolt are NOT clean single caster-picked types (Prismatic = per-color ray, not attacker's choice; Chaos Bolt = d8-rolled with a choice only on doubles) — options list the full set of damage types in play so a resistance resolver can consider all, but the attacker does not freely pick. Chaos Bolt, Sorcerous Burst, Spirit Shroud, Summon Dragon are PHB (not SRD 5.2); the rest are SRD 5.2."
